# NodeJS installation

1. Download a portable version
  - https://nodejs.org/dist/v24.11.1/node-v24.11.1-win-x64.zip
2. Extract the downloaded file (default path is ok)
3. Copy the extracted folder's absolute path e.g. `C:\Users\raymundoj\Downloads\node-v24.11.1-win-x64\node-v24.11.1-win-x64`
4. Click the Windows key
5. Search for "Edit environment variables for your account" 
6. Double-Click on "PATH" (upper portion)
7. Click on "New"
8. Paste the copied path from step #3
9. Click "Ok" (twice)
